=== Phase 4: Syntax Sugar - Complete Test ===

1. Auto-boxing in declarations:
  Int x = 42:      42
  Float f = 3.14:  3.14
  String s:        hello

2. Auto-boxing in assignments:
  y = 100:         100
  g = 2.71:        2.71

3. Operator overloading (arithmetic):
  15 + 7 = 22
  15 - 7 = 8
  15 * 7 = 105
  15 / 7 = 2
  15 % 7 = 1

4. Operator overloading (comparison):
  10 < 20:  true
  10 <= 20: true
  10 > 20:  false
  10 >= 20: false
  10 == 20: false
  10 != 20: true

5. String concatenation:
  Result: Hello, World!

6. Function calls with auto-boxing:
  add(5, 10):      15
  multiply(3, 7):  21

7. Return statement auto-boxing:
  getAnswer():     42

8. Integer caching (Phase 2):
  50 cached:       50
  50 cached again: 50
  128 cached:      128

9. Complex expression:
  (5 + 3) * 2 - 10 = 6

10. Comparison in control flow:
  Score 85 > 60: PASS
  Counted to: 5

11. Bool auto-boxing and operators:
  Bool isTrue = true:   true
  Bool isFalse = false: false
  true == true:  true
  true != false: true

12. Arrays with Box types:
  Int[] numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] (auto-boxed!)
  numbers[0] + numbers[1] = 3
  After numbers[2] = 10: 10
  Sum of all elements: 22
  Float[] prices = [9.99, 19.99, 29.99] (auto-boxed!)
  First price: 9.99
  Bool[] flags = [true, false, true] (auto-boxed!)
  First flag: true

13. Float auto-boxing and operators:
  PI * radius: 6.28318
  radius / 2: 1.0
  3.14159 > 2.0: true

14. Complex mixed operations:
  10^2 = 100 (greater than 50)
  multiply(100, 2) = 200
  200 is between 100 and 300: true

15. String auto-boxing and concatenation:
  Full name: John Doe
  Greeting: Hello, John Doe!

